{
  "key": "ontology:regulation",
  "label": "Regulation Ontology",
  "version": 1,
  "domain": "financial_services",
  "notes": "Volume XI Sprint-1 pack (ADR-0014/0015). Operational ontology for the U.S. financial-regulator graph and its supervisory artifacts: prudential regulators (NCUA/FDIC/Federal Reserve/OCC), the consumer bureau (CFPB), markets regulators (SEC/FINRA), housing/mortgage agencies and GSEs (FHA/VA/USDA/FHFA/Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac/Ginnie Mae), state regulators, and the supervisory cycle (call_reports/examinations/consent_orders). ncua, call_reports, and examinations are defined in the credit_union anchor pack and are referenced here as closed targets, not redefined. Relationship targets are catalog schema_refs (closed graph). Supervisory conclusions (ratings, findings, enforcement) persist evidence, source, confidence, and lineage — never weights alone (DOCTRINE; ADR-0005). Connector keys are forward references into the Connector Registry (Volume IX).",
  "ontologies": [
    {
      "object": "financial_services:regulation:fdic",
      "label": "FDIC (Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation)",
      "notes": "Insures deposits at banks/thrifts (DIF), is the primary federal regulator of state non-member banks, and resolves failed depositories.",
